                    {
                        "unit_id": 1012,
                        "title": "The Importance of Planning and Time Management",
                        "slug": "the-importance-of-planning-and-time-management",
                        "order": 20,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": "IZEuj-iL-2w",
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<h5>Planning and time management are essential skills in today’s workplace as we are getting more and more challenged to do more with less. Choosing what to focus on in our day to day work becomes a necessity that all employees, managers or entrepreneurs should master. In the coming videos, we will take you through a step by step process to determine what is important to you, how can you reflect that into your plan and how can you ensure that you will be doing what you planned for. As you then execute your plan on a day to day basis, you will get less stress, and much more satisfaction. As the saying goes “Failing to plan is planning to fail” so let’s start the planning course!</h5>",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "\"A goal without a plan is just a wish.\" Antoine de Saint-Exupery",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5><span id=\"yiv8655276729yui_3_16_0_ym19_1_1461734995029_12062\">Vera a 22 year old recent graduate working at a telecom operator, feels that she needs more time in her day to do what she needs to do. She is always rushing around, juggling between work and personal issues and at the end of the day, she feels that she hasn't done much. Very decides, she needs to take a step back and look at how she is spending her day and if it is aligned to her goals. </span></h5>",
                            "course-unit-last-related-content": "",
                            "course-unit-customrelated": "",
                            "course-unit-page-show-game": "",
                            "course-unit-page-show-related": "",
                            "course-unit-page-ads": "",
