                    {
                        "unit_id": 1015,
                        "title": "Setting your 1 Year Objectives",
                        "slug": "setting-your-1-year-objectives",
                        "order": 50,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": "czcgNiXpOP0",
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<h5>Keeping in mind what you want to achieve in 3 years, think of the concrete steps that you need to take in the coming year that would help you reach that 3 year objective. A good way to do so is to put one milestone that you want to accomplish each month along the year. Make sure that you are taking into account the 2 personal and 2 professional goals you had in your 3 year objectives.</h5>",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "\"Planning is bringing the future into the present so that you can do something about it now.\" Alan Lakein",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5>To reach her 3 year plan, Vera decides to try to find within her current company an opening in the Corporate Social Responsibility department and tries to identify and participate in volunteering activities that build her experience in community work. She also makes a list of friends who are in that field so that they can advise her and she learns more about that.</h5>",
